images.title: Bloom time for the Jacaranda
images.caption: Bloom time for the Jacaranda
images.desc: Though much of Australia is known for its variety of plant life, the Jacanarda is without question one of the most beloved. Commonly mistaken as a local Australian species, the Jacanarda’s roots lie in Brazil. Early sources believe that in around 1818 the Jacaranda mimosifolia species was collected and returned to the Royal Gardens at Kew, England, while plant hunter Allan Cunningham was sent on from Rio de Janeiro to New South Wales, where he would come to serve as a colonial botanist.
